<%!-- ============================================================
  How it works — the standalone, linkable explainer of the model,
  written for a first-time evaluator: the simplest true version of
  the product, one request traced start to finish.

  The example is the same story the /security hero shows — Maya
  Chen's Claude Code restarting checkout-api.service on api-iad-02,
  approved by Jordan Lee (both from the demo seed) — so the story
  holds across pages. Payload braces are HTML-escaped (&#123;/&#125;)
  because HEEx treats literal braces as interpolation; the colored
  spans follow the home page's code idiom (sky keys, brand strings,
  amber numbers/pending, rose deny).
============================================================ --%>
<div class="bg-zinc-950 text-zinc-100">
  <.marketing_nav current_user={@current_user} current={:how_it_works} />

  <%!-- Hero --%>
  <section class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-[#07080a]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24 sm:py-32 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-400">How it works</p>
      <.marketing_heading tag="h1" scale={:display} class="mt-2">
        Your agent requests. Your runner executes.
      </.marketing_heading>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-zinc-300">
        When your agent needs something done — say a service is failing and it wants to investigate —
        it doesn't open a shell or connect directly to the host. It asks emisar for one declared
        action, on one server, for a stated reason. Depending on your rules, that request runs right
        away, gets refused, or waits for a person to approve it. A small program on your server
        called the runner does the actual work, and every step is written down in the audit log.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- The three parts --%>
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white text-balance sm:text-4xl">
          The three pieces.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
          Your agent talks to emisar, and emisar talks to a small program you install on your
          servers — the runner. The runner only ever connects outward, the way a browser does,
          so there's no open port and nothing on the internet can reach into your hosts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mx-auto mt-12 grid max-w-3xl grid-cols-1 items-stretch gap-3 sm:grid-cols-[1fr_auto_1fr_auto_1fr]">
        <%= for {icon, label, sub} <- [
          {"hero-cpu-chip", "Your AI agent", "Claude, Cursor, ChatGPT — anything that speaks MCP"},
          {"hero-cloud", "Emisar cloud", "Your catalog, your rules, approvals, and the audit trail"},
          {"hero-server", "The runner", "A small program on your server that does the work"}
        ] do %>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/60 p-6 text-center">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-brand-500/10 text-brand-400">
              <.icon name={icon} class="h-5 w-5" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-4 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-50">{label}</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-5 text-zinc-400">{sub}</p>
          </div>
          <div :if={label != "The runner"} class="flex items-center justify-center text-zinc-700">
            <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="hidden h-5 w-5 sm:block" />
            <.icon name="hero-arrow-down" class="h-5 w-5 sm:hidden" />
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- One request, start to finish --%>
  <section class="border-y border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/40 py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white text-balance sm:text-4xl">
          One request, start to finish.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
          Here's a real one: checkout is failing, and the agent wants to restart the service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="mt-14">
        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-4 pb-12 sm:gap-x-6">
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-5 top-10 w-px bg-zinc-800" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-brand-500/25 bg-brand-500/10 font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">
            01
          </span>
          <div class="min-w-0">
            <h3 class="flex min-h-10 items-center text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-lg">
              The agent asks
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
              The agent can't run commands — asking is all it can do. The ask is one action from
              your catalog, the arguments to fill it in, and a reason a human can read later.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 max-w-2xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-900 bg-black/40">
              <div class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/80 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500">
                the request
              </div>
              <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-5 text-zinc-300">&#123;
  <span class="text-sky-300">"tool"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"run_action"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"action_id"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"systemd.unit_restart"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"args"</span>: &#123; <span class="text-sky-300">"unit"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"checkout-api.service"</span> &#125;,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"reason"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"checkout-api is returning 502s — restart it"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"runner"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"api-iad-02"</span>
&#125;</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-4 pb-12 sm:gap-x-6">
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-5 top-10 w-px bg-zinc-800" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-brand-500/25 bg-brand-500/10 font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">
            02
          </span>
          <div class="min-w-0">
            <h3 class="flex min-h-10 items-center text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-lg">
              emisar checks it
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
              Before your rules even come into it, emisar checks the basics: the action really
              is in your catalog, it comes from a pack your admin trusts — a pack whose content
              changed is blocked until someone re-approves it — the arguments fit the schema,
              and this agent is allowed to touch that server.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 max-w-2xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-900 bg-black/40">
              <div class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/80 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500">
                the checks
              </div>
              <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-5 text-zinc-300"><span class="text-brand-400">✓</span> <span class="text-zinc-500">action</span>   systemd.unit_restart <span class="text-zinc-500">— in your catalog</span>
<span class="text-brand-400">✓</span> <span class="text-zinc-500">pack</span>     linux @ 4e91ab27… <span class="text-zinc-500">— trusted by your admin</span>
<span class="text-brand-400">✓</span> <span class="text-zinc-500">args</span>     unit = <span class="text-brand-300">"checkout-api.service"</span> <span class="text-zinc-500">— fits the schema</span>
<span class="text-brand-400">✓</span> <span class="text-zinc-500">runner</span>   api-iad-02 <span class="text-zinc-500">— allowed for this agent</span></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-4 pb-12 sm:gap-x-6">
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-5 top-10 w-px bg-zinc-800" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-brand-500/25 bg-brand-500/10 font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">
            03
          </span>
          <div class="min-w-0">
            <h3 class="flex min-h-10 items-center text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-lg">
              Your rules decide
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
              This is where your policy comes in: it can let an action run freely, refuse it
              outright, or require a person to sign off. A service restart is disruptive enough
              that it waits — Jordan gets the approval, reads the reason, and taps Approve.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 max-w-2xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-900 bg-black/40">
              <div class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/80 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500">
                the decision
              </div>
              <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-5 text-zinc-300"><span class="text-zinc-500">policy</span>     Service restarts require approval
<span class="text-zinc-500">decision</span>   <span class="text-amber-300">require_approval</span> → waiting for a person
<span class="text-zinc-500">approved</span>   <span class="text-brand-300">Jordan Lee · 41 seconds later ✓</span></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-4 pb-12 sm:gap-x-6">
          <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-5 top-10 w-px bg-zinc-800" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-brand-500/25 bg-brand-500/10 font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">
            04
          </span>
          <div class="min-w-0">
            <h3 class="flex min-h-10 items-center text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-lg">
              The runner does the work
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
              The runner doesn't blindly trust the cloud. It re-checks the pack and the
              arguments on your own server, runs that one command — there's no shell involved —
              and scrubs anything that looks like a secret from the output before it leaves the
              machine.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 max-w-2xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-900 bg-black/40">
              <div class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/80 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500">
                on your server
              </div>
              <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-5 text-zinc-300"><span class="text-zinc-500">runner</span>   api-iad-02
<span class="text-zinc-500">check</span>    pack hash + arguments — verified again on the host <span class="text-brand-400">✓</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500">run</span>      <span class="text-zinc-600">$</span> <span class="text-zinc-100">systemctl restart checkout-api.service</span>
<span class="text-zinc-500">result</span>   exit <span class="text-amber-300">0</span> · 0.38s · secrets scrubbed from the output</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_minmax(0,1fr)] gap-x-4 sm:gap-x-6">
          <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-brand-500/25 bg-brand-500/10 font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-brand-400">
            05
          </span>
          <div class="min-w-0">
            <h3 class="flex min-h-10 items-center text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 sm:text-lg">
              Everything is on the record
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-400">
              The whole story — who asked, why, who approved, what ran, and what came back —
              lands in the audit trail. Each entry carries a hash of the one before it, so
              tampering shows. You can search it in the console or stream it to your SIEM.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 max-w-2xl overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-900 bg-black/40">
              <div class="border-b border-zinc-900 bg-zinc-950/80 px-4 py-2 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-zinc-500">
                the audit entry
              </div>
              <pre class="overflow-x-auto p-4 font-mono text-[11.5px] leading-5 text-zinc-300">&#123;
  <span class="text-sky-300">"event"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"execution_completed"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"action"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"systemd.unit_restart"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"requested_by"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"Maya Chen · Claude Code"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"approved_by"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"Jordan Lee"</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"exit_code"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">0</span>,
  <span class="text-sky-300">"prev_hash"</span>: <span class="text-brand-300">"9a72d4…"</span>
&#125;</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="mt-12 text-center text-sm">
        <.link
          navigate={~p"/security"}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 font-medium text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300"
        >
          And the host keeps the last word, even against a compromised cloud
          <.icon name="hero-arrow-right" class="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
        </.link>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <.marketing_cta
    headline="Run your first gated action in five minutes."
    subcopy="Install the runner, connect your agent, and put a real request through."
    secondary_label="Talk to sales"
    secondary_path={EmisarWeb.MailTo.sales()}
  />

  <.marketing_footer />
</div>
